If anyone is having an issue that has Acceleration installed and crashes when they use the "Ground Call" button after loading an IFR flight, it's a known bug in the final version of the product.  You can get around it by either:

 1.) Uninstalling Acceleration and using FSX updates Service Pack #1 & #2, **OR**
2.) As soon as you click "FLY" and load into the sim, SAVE your flight, quit FSX, reopen it, and LOAD your flight.

Either one takes care of the problem.  Another known bug for people with Acceleration installed that you cannot get around is the FMC will lose it's PERF INIT settings after you start the engines and you will have to enter them again.  The only way around this is to program the PERF INIT into the FMC after the engines are started.
